    heading: About this component
    text: This is a simple system that allows you to add Readme in asset format to
      the project and scene objects.
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - name: Header -How it works
    heading: How it works
    text: "To create a Readme file: \n\n1 - <b>Right Click</b> in <b>Project</b>
      view\r\n\r\n2 - Select: <b>Create => Readme</b>, in the context menu.\r\n\r\n3
      - A Readme file will be created in the selected folder"
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - name: Header -Add It to...
    heading: Add It to Scene
    text: '1 - Create a readme in advance, following the previous tips.

      

      2
      - Select some GameObject at Scene and add the componnent (Readme);

      

      3
      - At the component, select the Readme file to show.

      

      4 - Uncheck
      the <b>Change Readme File</b> box.

      

      5 - Check <b>Change Readme
      File</b>, if you want change the readme reference of this component.'
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - name: Header -Setup a r...
    heading: Setup a root Readme
    text: "A root Readme is a file that will be showed every time you launch the
      project. \n\nTo do so you have to check <b>Set as Root</b> in your Readme file "
